args: Aaaah ha ha ha! We did it! WE DID IT!
We did it, Audric! We killed the witch!
Now you don't have to leave us!
We did it for you, Audric!
I have to find Cassandra! Now!
Well, look who it is... *cough*\nL-looks like I made a miscalculation...
What happened here, Cassandra?!\nYou should have been able to dispatch\nthat mob with ease!
What is this? A magical grimoire?
It c-contains a ritual...to sever\na chain of causality...
You gave your life for a BOOK?!\nOh, you old fool...
Don't be absurd...who dies for a book?\nIt was...all for you...
I've had a good run...in this old world...\nIf I can end it in your arms one last time, \nI'll end it happily...
We did it for you, Audric!
That witch was going to trick you!\nShe would have sent you away!
That's why we killed her! For you!
Now you can stay with us!
THAT is why you killed Cassandra?!\nWhy you killed Notte?!
Your crimes are unforgivable...\nand they will be judged!
B-but...we did it for you!\nWe thought you'd be happy!
No one asked you to do ANYTHING for me,\nmuch less commit murder!
And so what if we have?!
We have no kingdom anymore! No law!\nEven if we have committed a crime,\nthere exist none to judge our actions!
Then I shall be your judge!
I am Aurelius, the last king of Alberia,\nand by that name do I condemn you all!
B-but...but why?! We did it for you!
You did it for YOURSELVES! You are a\nscared, feckless band of sheep who\nonly wanted to stop me from leaving!
You sacrificed innocents in an attempt to\nsave yourselves and now seek to shift\nthe blame away!
And yes, I may share some fault in this.\nIt was I who raised your hopes, after all.
Therefore, my judgment will be for you to\nlive on your own, without me.
So you won't help us anymore?!
You can't cast us aside like this!\nWhere are we supposed to go?!
What if the Empire attacks us?\nAre you going to let that happen?!\nYou're supposed to be HELPING us!
In fact, I bet the Empire would look kindly\non the people who delivered the head of\nAlberia's king to their gates!
If you are fool enough to come for me,\nI will show you no mercy.
It's your fault... You're making us do this\nby casting us away...
...This is what my sins have wrought.
My allies all dead, and myself betrayed\nby the very people I was sworn to protect.
Perhaps this world does not need my aid.
No. I will not stop. I will NEVER stop.
All I can do is carry my crimes, my hope,\nand my despair ever forward.
Come, Zodiark. A new world awaits.
I can't stop thinking about how things\nare going in that world right now.\nAnd about how Audric is doing...
Uh, so I don't wanna interrupt your sad\ntrailing-off thing, but someone's coming.
